{
  "text": "Of particular interest for our subsequent work will be scenarios involving noisy communications links and time-varying measurement objectives. This can be achieved by using adaptive subgradient methods that harness interference for computation [CITATION_1] . Also, by using more knowledge about the target application and leveraging ideas from compressed sensing, the number of required measurements in the network can be reduced. In turn, this will result in additional savings in energy consumption and introduce new degrees of freedom to the tradeoff between convergence speed and estimation accuracy on one hand, and energy consumption and network robustness on the other hand.",
  "citation_candidates": [
